{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_7","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '120,320p' legs_log.md\"","aggregated_output":"    * the mark-colour = least-common non-centre cell computation (TWICE),\n    * the block-centre -> (x, y) click conversion (c + s//2 - 1, r + s//2 - 1)\n      (open-coded in three places), and\n    * reading a block's current centre colour.\n- Extracted each as a shared, named leg, WRITTEN ONCE: pattern_key_grid (perceive\n  + guard), read_mini_key (was cell3), mark_color, block_click_xy,\n  block_center_color, and key_marked_neighbours (yield each mini-key's marked\n  neighbour + that key's centre colour — the \"read the marks\" step level 4 needs).\n  Both decoders now compose these; only their genuinely different DECODE RULE\n  remains inline (level 3: a 2-state toggle predicate over ALL neighbours keyed on\n  block colour; level 4: marked-neighbour -> centre colour + one shared default,\n  driven by click-cycle distance). Behaviour unchanged (levels=4, moves=46,\n  replay_ok=True): pure refactor, no new clicks.\n\n## Candidate higher-order leg: decode_pattern_key(env, rule) — parameterised decoder\n- The recurring composition across levels 3 and 4 is a pattern-key DECODE pipeline:\n    perceive lattice (pattern_key_grid) -> read mini-keys (read_mini_key) ->\n    find the mark colour (mark_color) -> apply a per-neighbour RULE to derive a\n    per-block goal -> turn goals into block-centre clicks (block_click_xy) ->\n    hand the click list to solve_click_board(env, planner).\n  The ONLY per-level variation is the RULE that maps (mini-keys, mark, current\n  block colours) to a per-block target/selection, plus how a target becomes a\n  click count (1 click for the 2-state toggle, cycle-distance clicks for k-state).\n- Candidate leg shape: decode_pattern_key(env, rule) where `rule(grid, mark,\n  frame) -> {block_idx: click_count}` returns how many clicks each block needs;\n  the leg builds the flat click list via block_click_xy and returns it, so every\n  pattern-key planner collapses to supplying `rule`. Not promoted yet: the two\n  rules are still structurally different (level 3 keys on block colour over ALL\n  neighbours and toggles; level 4 keys only on MARKED neighbours over a colour\n  cycle with a searched default), so forcing one signature now risks over-fitting.\n  If a THIRD pattern-key variant appears and reuses this skeleton, promote\n  decode_pattern_key from candidate to a load-bearing shared leg (the pattern-key\n  analogue of solve_click_board for the coordinate-click substrate).\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_8","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '350,620p' legs.py\"","aggregated_output":"\ndef solve_multistate_key_board(env):\n    \"\"\"Decode a multi-state pattern-key board (cells cycle through k colours) and\n    commit the completing block clicks. Thin composition of solve_click_board over\n    the multi-state pattern-key planner.\"\"\"\n    return solve_click_board(env, discover_multistate_key_clicks)\n\n\ndef _gf2_solution(matrix, rhs, nvars):\n    \"\"\"Solve a binary linear system, choosing zero for every free variable.\"\"\"\n    a = [list(row) + [int(value)] for row, value in zip(matrix, rhs)]\n    pivots = []\n    row = 0\n    for col in range(nvars):\n        pivot = next((r for r in range(row, len(a)) if a[r][col]), None)\n        if pivot is None:\n            continue\n        a[row], a[pivot] = a[pivot], a[row]\n        for r in range(len(a)):\n            if r != row and a[r][col]:\n                a[r] = [x ^ y for x, y in zip(a[r], a[row])]\n        pivots.append(col)\n        row += 1\n    if any(not any(r[:-1]) and r[-1] for r in a):\n        return None\n    out = [0] * nvars\n    for r, col in enumerate(pivots):\n        out[col] = a[r][-1]\n    return out\n\n\ndef discover_coupled_key_clicks(env):\n    \"\"\"Plan a binary pattern-key board whose clicks may toggle several blocks.\n\n    Some decorated blocks are inert clues. Their two neighbour symbols mean\n    SAME/OPPOSITE relative to the clue's binary centre colour. Other decorated\n    blocks are controls whose click effects are discovered on clones, just like\n    the ordinary one-block controls. The decoded target constraints and observed\n    click-effect matrix form a GF(2) system. Both possible SAME symbols are tried\n    on clones; the reward identifies the correct interpretation. Unclued cells\n    remain unconstrained. Returns the first reward-reaching click prefix.\n    \"\"\"\n    g = pattern_key_grid(env)\n    if not g:\n        return None\n    s, bg, slots, uniform, patterns = g\n    frame = np.asarray(env.frame())\n    active = []\n    effects = {}\n    state_colours = set()\n\n    # Discover which slots are controls and the parity effect of each click.\n    for idx in sorted(slots):\n        clone = env.clone()\n        x, y = block_click_xy(slots, idx, s)\n        clone.step(6, x, y)\n        changed = {\n            other for other in slots\n            if block_center_color(frame, slots, other, s)\n            != block_center_color(clone.frame(), slots, other, s)\n        }\n        if not changed:\n            continue\n        active.append(idx)\n        effects[idx] = changed\n        for other in changed:\n            state_colours.add(block_center_color(frame, slots, other, s))\n            state_colours.add(block_center_color(clone.frame(), slots, other, s))\n\n    inert_clues = sorted(set(patterns) - set(active))\n    states = sorted(state_colours)\n    if not active or not inert_clues or len(states) != 2:\n        return None\n\n    # Each active neighbour may be described by several overlapping clues.\n    observations = {}\n    for idx in inert_clues:\n        gg = read_mini_key(patterns[idx])\n        center = block_center_color(frame, slots, idx, s)\n        if center not in states:\n            continue\n        for di in range(-1, 2):\n            for dj in range(-1, 2):\n                if (di, dj) == (0, 0):\n                    continue\n                other = (idx[0] + di, idx[1] + dj)\n                if other in effects:\n                    observations.setdefault(other, []).append(\n                        (gg[di + 1][dj + 1], center)\n                    )\n    tokens = sorted({token for obs in observations.values() for token, _ in obs})\n    if len(tokens) != 2:\n        return None\n\n    base_level = env.levels_completed\n    for same_token in tokens:\n        targets = {}\n        consistent = True\n        for cell, obs in observations.items():\n            wanted = set()\n            for token, center in obs:\n                opposite = states[1] if center == states[0] else states[0]\n                wanted.add(center if token == same_token else opposite)\n            if len(wanted) != 1:\n                consistent = False\n                break\n            targets[cell] = next(iter(wanted))\n        if not consistent or not targets:\n            continue\n\n        cells = sorted(targets)\n        matrix = [\n            [int(cell in effects[action]) for action in active]\n            for cell in cells\n        ]\n        rhs = [\n            int(block_center_color(frame, slots, cell, s) != targets[cell])\n            for cell in cells\n        ]\n        solution = _gf2_solution(matrix, rhs, len(active))\n        if solution is None:\n            continue\n\n        clicks = [\n            block_click_xy(slots, action, s)\n            for action, take in zip(active, solution) if take\n        ]\n        clone = env.clone()\n        prefix = []\n        for click in clicks:\n            x, y = click\n            clone.step(6, x, y)\n            prefix.append(click)\n            if clone.levels_completed > base_level:\n                return prefix\n    return None\n\n\ndef solve_coupled_key_board(env):\n    \"\"\"Decode and solve a binary key board with coupled toggle controls.\"\"\"\n    return solve_click_board(env, discover_coupled_key_clicks)\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
